3/*++
4/* NAME
5/* postconf_master 3
6/* SUMMARY
7/* support for master.cf
8/* SYNOPSIS
9/* #include <postconf.h>
10/*
11/* const char pcf_daemon_options_expecting_value[];
12/*
13/* void pcf_read_master(fail_on_open)
14/* int fail_on_open;
15/*
16/* void pcf_show_master_entries(fp, mode, service_filters)
17/* VSTREAM *fp;
18/* int mode;
19/* char **service_filters;
20/*
21/* void pcf_show_master_fields(fp, mode, n_filters, field_filters)
22/* VSTREAM *fp;
23/* int mode;
24/* int n_filters;
25/* char **field_filters;
26/*
27/* void pcf_edit_master_field(masterp, field, new_value)
28/* PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp;
29/* int field;
30/* const char *new_value;
31/*
32/* void pcf_show_master_params(fp, mode, argc, **param_filters)
33/* VSTREAM *fp;
34/* int mode;
35/* int argc;
36/* char **param_filters;
37/*
38/* void pcf_edit_master_param(masterp, mode, param_name, param_value)
39/* PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp;
40/* int mode;
41/* const char *param_name;
42/* const char *param_value;
43/* AUXILIARY FUNCTIONS
44/* const char *pcf_parse_master_entry(masterp, buf)
45/* PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp;
46/* const char *buf;
47/*
48/* void pcf_print_master_entry(fp, mode, masterp)
49/* VSTREAM *fp;
50/* int mode;
51/* PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp;
52/*
53/* void pcf_free_master_entry(masterp)
54/* PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp;
55/* DESCRIPTION
56/* pcf_read_master() reads entries from master.cf into memory.
57/*
58/* pcf_show_master_entries() writes the entries in the master.cf
59/* file to the specified stream.
60/*
61/* pcf_show_master_fields() writes name/type/field=value records
62/* to the specified stream.
63/*
64/* pcf_edit_master_field() updates the value of a single-column
65/* or multi-column attribute.
66/*
67/* pcf_show_master_params() writes name/type/parameter=value
68/* records to the specified stream.
69/*
70/* pcf_edit_master_param() updates, removes or adds the named
71/* parameter in a master.cf entry (the remove request ignores
72/* the parameter value).
73/*
74/* pcf_daemon_options_expecting_value[] is an array of master.cf
75/* daemon command-line options that expect an option value.
76/*
77/* pcf_parse_master_entry() parses a (perhaps multi-line)
78/* string that contains a complete master.cf entry, and
79/* normalizes daemon command-line options to simplify further
80/* handling.
81/*
82/* pcf_print_master_entry() prints a parsed master.cf entry.
83/*
84/* pcf_free_master_entry() returns storage to the heap that
85/* was allocated by pcf_parse_master_entry().
86/*
87/* Arguments
88/* .IP fail_on_open
89/* Specify FAIL_ON_OPEN if open failure is a fatal error,
90/* WARN_ON_OPEN if a warning should be logged instead.
91/* .IP fp
92/* Output stream.
93/* .IP mode
94/* Bit-wise OR of flags. Flags other than the following are
95/* ignored.
96/* .RS
97/* .IP PCF_FOLD_LINE
98/* Wrap long output lines.
99/* .IP PCF_SHOW_EVAL
100/* Expand $name in parameter values.
101/* .IP PCF_EDIT_EXCL
102/* Request that pcf_edit_master_param() removes the parameter.
103/* .RE
104/* .IP n_filters
105/* The number of command-line filters.
106/* .IP field_filters
107/* A list of zero or more service field patterns (name/type/field).
108/* The output is formatted as "name/type/field = value". If
109/* no filters are specified, pcf_show_master_fields() outputs
110/* the fields of all master.cf entries in the specified order.
111/* .IP param_filters
112/* A list of zero or more service parameter patterns
113/* (name/type/parameter). The output is formatted as
114/* "name/type/parameter = value". If no filters are specified,
115/* pcf_show_master_params() outputs the parameters of all
116/* master.cf entries in sorted order.
117/* .IP service_filters
118/* A list of zero or more service patterns (name or name/type).
119/* If no filters are specified, pcf_show_master_entries()
120/* outputs all master.cf entries in the specified order.
121/* .IP field
122/* Index into parsed master.cf entry.
123/* .IP new_value
124/* Replacement value for the specified field. It is split in
125/* whitespace in case of a multi-field attribute.
126/* DIAGNOSTICS
127/* Problems are reported to the standard error stream.
128/* LICENSE
129/* .ad
130/* .fi
131/* The Secure Mailer license must be distributed with this software.
132/* AUTHOR(S)
133/* Wietse Venema
134/* IBM T.J. Watson Research
135/* P.O. Box 704
136/* Yorktown Heights, NY 10598, USA
137/*
138/* Wietse Venema
139/* Google, Inc.
140/* 111 8th Avenue
141/* New York, NY 10011, USA
142/*--*/

174const char pcf_daemon_options_expecting_value[] = "o";
175
176 /*
177 * Data structure to capture a command-line service field filter.
178 */
179typedef struct {
180 int match_count; /* hit count */
181 const char *raw_text; /* full pattern text */
182 ARGV *service_pattern; /* parsed service name, type, ... */
183 int field_pattern; /* parsed field pattern */
184 const char *param_pattern; /* parameter pattern */
185} PCF_MASTER_FLD_REQ;
186
187 /*
188 * Valid inputs.
189 */
190static const char *pcf_valid_master_types[] = {
191 MASTER_XPORT_NAME_UNIX,
192 MASTER_XPORT_NAME_FIFO,
193 MASTER_XPORT_NAME_INET,
194 MASTER_XPORT_NAME_PASS,
195 0,
196};
197
198static const char pcf_valid_bool_types[] = "yn-";
199
200#define STR(x) vstring_str(x)
201
202/* pcf_extract_field - extract text from {}, trim leading/trailing blanks */
203
204static void pcf_extract_field(ARGV *argv, int field, const char *parens)
205{
206 char *arg = argv->argv[field];
207 char *err;
208
209 if ((err = extpar(&arg, parens, EXTPAR_FLAG_STRIP)) != 0) {
210 msg_warn("%s: %s", MASTER_CONF_FILE, err);
211 myfree(err);
212 }
213 argv_replace_one(argv, field, arg);
214}
215
216/* pcf_normalize_nameval - normalize name = value from inside {} */
217
218static void pcf_normalize_nameval(ARGV *argv, int field)
219{
220 char *arg = argv->argv[field];
221 char *name;
222 char *value;
223 const char *err;
224 char *normalized;
225
226 if ((err = split_nameval(arg, &name, &value)) != 0) {
227 msg_warn("%s: %s: \"%s\"", MASTER_CONF_FILE, err, arg);
228 } else {
229 normalized = concatenate(name, "=", value, (char *) 0);
230 argv_replace_one(argv, field, normalized);
231 myfree(normalized);
232 }
233}
234
235/* pcf_normalize_daemon_args - bring daemon arguments into canonical form */
236
237static void pcf_normalize_daemon_args(ARGV *argv)
238{
239 int field;
240 char *arg;
241 char *cp;
242 char *junk;
243 int extract_field;
244
245 /*
246 * Normalize options to simplify later processing.
247 */
248 for (field = PCF_MASTER_MIN_FIELDS; argv->argv[field] != 0; field++) {
249 arg = argv->argv[field];
250 if (arg[0] != '-' || strcmp(arg, "--") == 0)
251 break;
252 for (cp = arg + 1; *cp; cp++) {
253 if (strchr(pcf_daemon_options_expecting_value, *cp) != 0
254 && cp > arg + 1) {
255 /* Split "-stuffozz" into "-stuff" and "-ozz". */
256 junk = concatenate("-", cp, (char *) 0);
257 argv_insert_one(argv, field + 1, junk);
258 myfree(junk);
259 *cp = 0; /* XXX argv_replace_one() */
260 break;
261 }
262 }
263 if (strchr(pcf_daemon_options_expecting_value, arg[1]) == 0)
264 /* Option requires no value. */
265 continue;
266 if (arg[2] != 0) {
267 /* Split "-oname=value" into "-o" "name=value". */
268 argv_insert_one(argv, field + 1, arg + 2);
269 arg[2] = 0; /* XXX argv_replace_one() */
270 field += 1;
271 extract_field = (argv->argv[field][0] == CHARS_BRACE[0]);
272 } else if (argv->argv[field + 1] != 0) {
273 /* Already in "-o" "name=value" form. */
274 field += 1;
275 extract_field = (argv->argv[field][0] == CHARS_BRACE[0]);
276 } else
277 extract_field = 0;
278 /* Extract text inside {}, optionally convert to name=value. */
279 if (extract_field) {
280 pcf_extract_field(argv, field, CHARS_BRACE);
281 if (argv->argv[field - 1][1] == 'o')
282 pcf_normalize_nameval(argv, field);
283 }
284 }
285 /* Normalize non-option arguments. */
286 for ( /* void */ ; argv->argv[field] != 0; field++)
287 /* Extract text inside {}. */
288 if (argv->argv[field][0] == CHARS_BRACE[0])
289 pcf_extract_field(argv, field, CHARS_BRACE);
290}
291
292/* pcf_fix_fatal - fix multiline text before release */
293
294static NORETURN PRINTFLIKE(1, 2) pcf_fix_fatal(const char *fmt,...)
295{
296 VSTRING *buf = vstring_alloc(100);
297 va_list ap;
298
299 /*
300 * Replace newline with whitespace.
301 */
302 va_start(ap, fmt);
303 vstring_vsprintf(buf, fmt, ap);
304 va_end(ap);
305 translit(STR(buf), "\n", " ");
306 msg_fatal("%s", STR(buf));
307 /* NOTREACHED */
308}
309
310/* pcf_check_master_entry - sanity check master.cf entry */
311
312static void pcf_check_master_entry(ARGV *argv, const char *raw_text)
313{
314 const char **cpp;
315 char *cp;
316 int len;
317 int field;
318
319 cp = argv->argv[PCF_MASTER_FLD_TYPE];
320 for (cpp = pcf_valid_master_types; /* see below */ ; cpp++) {
321 if (*cpp == 0)
322 pcf_fix_fatal("invalid " PCF_MASTER_NAME_TYPE " field \"%s\" in \"%s\"",
323 cp, raw_text);
324 if (strcmp(*cpp, cp) == 0)
325 break;
326 }
327
328 for (field = PCF_MASTER_FLD_PRIVATE; field <= PCF_MASTER_FLD_CHROOT; field++) {
329 cp = argv->argv[field];
330 if (cp[1] != 0 || strchr(pcf_valid_bool_types, *cp) == 0)
331 pcf_fix_fatal("invalid %s field \"%s\" in \"%s\"",
332 pcf_str_field_pattern(field), cp, raw_text);
333 }
334
335 cp = argv->argv[PCF_MASTER_FLD_WAKEUP];
336 len = strlen(cp);
337 if (len > 0 && cp[len - 1] == '?')
338 len--;
339 if (!(cp[0] == '-' && len == 1) && strspn(cp, "0123456789") != len)
340 pcf_fix_fatal("invalid " PCF_MASTER_NAME_WAKEUP " field \"%s\" in \"%s\"",
341 cp, raw_text);
342
343 cp = argv->argv[PCF_MASTER_FLD_MAXPROC];
344 if (strcmp("-", cp) != 0 && cp[strspn(cp, "0123456789")] != 0)
345 pcf_fix_fatal("invalid " PCF_MASTER_NAME_MAXPROC " field \"%s\" in \"%s\"",
346 cp, raw_text);
347}
348
349/* pcf_free_master_entry - destroy parsed entry */
350
351void pcf_free_master_entry(PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp)
352{
353 /* XX Fixme: allocation/deallocation asymmetry. */
354 myfree(masterp->name_space);
355 argv_free(masterp->argv);
356 if (masterp->valid_names)
357 htable_free(masterp->valid_names, myfree);
358 if (masterp->all_params)
359 dict_free(masterp->all_params);
360 myfree((void *) masterp);
361}
362
363/* pcf_parse_master_entry - parse one master line */
364
365const char *pcf_parse_master_entry(PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp, const char *buf)
366{
367 ARGV *argv;
368
369 /*
370 * We can't use the master daemon's master_ent routines in their current
371 * form. They convert everything to internal form, and they skip disabled
372 * services.
373 *
374 * The postconf command needs to show default fields as "-", and needs to
375 * know about all service names so that it can generate service-dependent
376 * parameter names (transport-dependent etc.).
377 *
378 * XXX Do per-field sanity checks.
379 */
380 argv = argv_splitq(buf, PCF_MASTER_BLANKS, CHARS_BRACE);
381 if (argv->argc < PCF_MASTER_MIN_FIELDS) {
382 argv_free(argv); /* Coverity 201311 */
383 return ("bad field count");
384 }
385 pcf_check_master_entry(argv, buf);
386 pcf_normalize_daemon_args(argv);
387 masterp->name_space =
388 concatenate(argv->argv[0], PCF_NAMESP_SEP_STR, argv->argv[1], (char *) 0);
389 masterp->argv = argv;
390 masterp->valid_names = 0;
391 masterp->all_params = 0;
392 return (0);
393}
394
395/* pcf_read_master - read and digest the master.cf file */
396
397void pcf_read_master(int fail_on_open_error)
398{
399 const char *myname = "pcf_read_master";
400 char *path;
401 VSTRING *buf;
402 VSTREAM *fp;
403 const char *err;
404 int entry_count = 0;
405 int line_count;
406 int last_line = 0;
407
408 /*
409 * Sanity check.
410 */
411 if (pcf_master_table != 0)
412 msg_panic("%s: master table is already initialized", myname);
413
414 /*
415 * Get the location of master.cf.
416 */
417 if (var_config_dir == 0)
418 pcf_set_config_dir();
419 path = concatenate(var_config_dir, "/", MASTER_CONF_FILE, (char *) 0);
420
421 /*
422 * Initialize the in-memory master table.
423 */
424 pcf_master_table = (PCF_MASTER_ENT *) mymalloc(sizeof(*pcf_master_table));
425
426 /*
427 * Skip blank lines and comment lines. Degrade gracefully if master.cf is
428 * not available, and master.cf is not the primary target.
429 */
430 if ((fp = vstream_fopen(path, O_RDONLY, 0)) == 0) {
431 if (fail_on_open_error)
432 msg_fatal("open %s: %m", path);
433 msg_warn("open %s: %m", path);
434 } else {
435 buf = vstring_alloc(100);
436 while (readllines(buf, fp, &last_line, &line_count) != 0) {
437 pcf_master_table = (PCF_MASTER_ENT *) myrealloc((void *) pcf_master_table,
438 (entry_count + 2) * sizeof(*pcf_master_table));
439 if ((err = pcf_parse_master_entry(pcf_master_table + entry_count,
440 STR(buf))) != 0)
441 msg_fatal("file %s: line %d: %s", path, line_count, err);
442 entry_count += 1;
443 }
444 vstream_fclose(fp);
445 vstring_free(buf);
446 }
447
448 /*
449 * Null-terminate the master table and clean up.
450 */
451 pcf_master_table[entry_count].argv = 0;
452 myfree(path);
453}
454
455/* pcf_print_master_entry - print one master line */
456
457void pcf_print_master_entry(VSTREAM *fp, int mode, PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp)
458{
459 char **argv = masterp->argv->argv;
460 const char *arg;
461 const char *aval;
462 int arg_len;
463 int line_len;
464 int field;
465 int in_daemon_options;
466 int need_parens;
467 static int column_goal[] = {
468 0, /* service */
469 11, /* type */
470 17, /* private */
471 25, /* unpriv */
472 33, /* chroot */
473 41, /* wakeup */
474 49, /* maxproc */
475 57, /* command */
476 };
477
478#define ADD_TEXT(text, len) do { \
479 vstream_fputs(text, fp); line_len += len; } \
480 while (0)
481#define ADD_SPACE ADD_TEXT(" ", 1)
482
483 /*
484 * Show the standard fields at their preferred column position. Use at
485 * least one-space column separation.
486 */
487 for (line_len = 0, field = 0; field < PCF_MASTER_MIN_FIELDS; field++) {
488 arg = argv[field];
489 if (line_len > 0) {
490 do {
491 ADD_SPACE;
492 } while (line_len < column_goal[field]);
493 }
494 ADD_TEXT(arg, strlen(arg));
495 }
496
497 /*
498 * Format the daemon command-line options and non-option arguments. Here,
499 * we have no data-dependent preference for column positions, but we do
500 * have argument grouping preferences.
501 */
502 in_daemon_options = 1;
503 for ( /* void */ ; (arg = argv[field]) != 0; field++) {
504 arg_len = strlen(arg);
505 aval = 0;
506 need_parens = 0;
507 if (in_daemon_options) {
508
509 /*
510 * Try to show the generic options (-v -D) on the first line, and
511 * non-options on a later line.
512 */
513 if (arg[0] != '-' || strcmp(arg, "--") == 0) {
514 in_daemon_options = 0;
515#if 0
516 if (mode & PCF_FOLD_LINE)
517 /* Force line wrap. */
518 line_len = PCF_LINE_LIMIT;
519#endif
520 }
521
522 /*
523 * Special processing for options that require a value.
524 */
525 else if (strchr(pcf_daemon_options_expecting_value, arg[1]) != 0
526 && (aval = argv[field + 1]) != 0) {
527
528 /* Force line wrap before option with value. */
529 line_len = PCF_LINE_LIMIT;
530
531 /*
532 * Optionally, expand $name in parameter value.
533 */
534 if (strcmp(arg, "-o") == 0
535 && (mode & PCF_SHOW_EVAL) != 0)
536 aval = pcf_expand_parameter_value((VSTRING *) 0, mode,
537 aval, masterp);
538
539 /*
540 * Keep option and value on the same line.
541 */
542 arg_len += strlen(aval) + 3;
543 if ((need_parens = aval[strcspn(aval, PCF_MASTER_BLANKS)]) != 0)
544 arg_len += 2;
545 }
546 } else {
547 need_parens = arg[strcspn(arg, PCF_MASTER_BLANKS)];
548 }
549
550 /*
551 * Insert a line break when the next item won't fit.
552 */
553 if (line_len > PCF_INDENT_LEN) {
554 if ((mode & PCF_FOLD_LINE) == 0
555 || line_len + 1 + arg_len < PCF_LINE_LIMIT) {
556 ADD_SPACE;
557 } else {
558 vstream_fputs("\n" PCF_INDENT_TEXT, fp);
559 line_len = PCF_INDENT_LEN;
560 }
561 }
562 if (in_daemon_options == 0 && need_parens)
563 ADD_TEXT("{", 1);
564 ADD_TEXT(arg, strlen(arg));
565 if (in_daemon_options == 0 && need_parens)
566 ADD_TEXT("}", 1);
567 if (aval) {
568 ADD_TEXT(" ", 1);
569 if (need_parens)
570 ADD_TEXT("{", 1);
571 ADD_TEXT(aval, strlen(aval));
572 if (need_parens)
573 ADD_TEXT("}", 1);
574 field += 1;
575
576 /* Force line wrap after option with value. */
577 line_len = PCF_LINE_LIMIT;
578
579 }
580 }
581 vstream_fputs("\n", fp);
582
583 if (msg_verbose)
584 vstream_fflush(fp);
585}
586
587/* pcf_show_master_entries - show master.cf entries */
588
589void pcf_show_master_entries(VSTREAM *fp, int mode, int argc, char **argv)
590{
591 PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp;
592 PCF_MASTER_FLD_REQ *field_reqs;
593 PCF_MASTER_FLD_REQ *req;
594
595 /*
596 * Parse the filter expressions.
597 */
598 if (argc > 0) {
599 field_reqs = (PCF_MASTER_FLD_REQ *)
600 mymalloc(sizeof(*field_reqs) * argc);
601 for (req = field_reqs; req < field_reqs + argc; req++) {
602 req->match_count = 0;
603 req->raw_text = *argv++;
604 req->service_pattern =
605 pcf_parse_service_pattern(req->raw_text, 1, 2);
606 if (req->service_pattern == 0)
607 msg_fatal("-M option requires service_name[/type]");
608 }
609 }
610
611 /*
612 * Iterate over the master table.
613 */
614 for (masterp = pcf_master_table; masterp->argv != 0; masterp++) {
615 if (argc > 0) {
616 for (req = field_reqs; req < field_reqs + argc; req++) {
617 if (PCF_MATCH_SERVICE_PATTERN(req->service_pattern,
618 masterp->argv->argv[0],
619 masterp->argv->argv[1])) {
620 req->match_count++;
621 pcf_print_master_entry(fp, mode, masterp);
622 }
623 }
624 } else {
625 pcf_print_master_entry(fp, mode, masterp);
626 }
627 }
628
629 /*
630 * Cleanup.
631 */
632 if (argc > 0) {
633 for (req = field_reqs; req < field_reqs + argc; req++) {
634 if (req->match_count == 0)
635 msg_warn("unmatched request: \"%s\"", req->raw_text);
636 argv_free(req->service_pattern);
637 }
638 myfree((void *) field_reqs);
639 }
640}
641
642/* pcf_print_master_field - scaffolding */
643
644static void pcf_print_master_field(VSTREAM *fp, int mode,
645 PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp,
646 int field)
647{
648 char **argv = masterp->argv->argv;
649 const char *arg;
650 const char *aval;
651 int arg_len;
652 int line_len;
653 int in_daemon_options;
654 int need_parens;
655
656 /*
657 * Show the field value, or the first value in the case of a multi-column
658 * field.
659 */
660#define ADD_CHAR(ch) ADD_TEXT((ch), 1)
661
662 line_len = 0;
663 if ((mode & PCF_HIDE_NAME) == 0) {
664 ADD_TEXT(argv[0], strlen(argv[0]));
665 ADD_CHAR(PCF_NAMESP_SEP_STR);
666 ADD_TEXT(argv[1], strlen(argv[1]));
667 ADD_CHAR(PCF_NAMESP_SEP_STR);
668 ADD_TEXT(pcf_str_field_pattern(field), strlen(pcf_str_field_pattern(field)));
669 }
670 if ((mode & (PCF_HIDE_NAME | PCF_HIDE_VALUE)) == 0) {
671 ADD_TEXT(" = ", 3);
672 }
673 if ((mode & PCF_HIDE_VALUE) == 0) {
674 if (line_len > 0 && line_len + strlen(argv[field]) > PCF_LINE_LIMIT) {
675 vstream_fputs("\n" PCF_INDENT_TEXT, fp);
676 line_len = PCF_INDENT_LEN;
677 }
678 ADD_TEXT(argv[field], strlen(argv[field]));
679 }
680
681 /*
682 * Format the daemon command-line options and non-option arguments. Here,
683 * we have no data-dependent preference for column positions, but we do
684 * have argument grouping preferences.
685 */
686 if (field == PCF_MASTER_FLD_CMD && (mode & PCF_HIDE_VALUE) == 0) {
687 in_daemon_options = 1;
688 for (field += 1; (arg = argv[field]) != 0; field++) {
689 arg_len = strlen(arg);
690 aval = 0;
691 need_parens = 0;
692 if (in_daemon_options) {
693
694 /*
695 * We make no special case for generic options (-v -D)
696 * options.
697 */
698 if (arg[0] != '-' || strcmp(arg, "--") == 0) {
699 in_daemon_options = 0;
700 } else if (strchr(pcf_daemon_options_expecting_value, arg[1]) != 0
701 && (aval = argv[field + 1]) != 0) {
702
703 /* Force line break before option with value. */
704 line_len = PCF_LINE_LIMIT;
705
706 /*
707 * Optionally, expand $name in parameter value.
708 */
709 if (strcmp(arg, "-o") == 0
710 && (mode & PCF_SHOW_EVAL) != 0)
711 aval = pcf_expand_parameter_value((VSTRING *) 0, mode,
712 aval, masterp);
713
714 /*
715 * Keep option and value on the same line.
716 */
717 arg_len += strlen(aval) + 1;
718 if ((need_parens = aval[strcspn(aval, PCF_MASTER_BLANKS)]) != 0)
719 arg_len += 2;
720 }
721 } else {
722 need_parens = arg[strcspn(arg, PCF_MASTER_BLANKS)];
723 }
724
725 /*
726 * Insert a line break when the next item won't fit.
727 */
728 if (line_len > PCF_INDENT_LEN) {
729 if ((mode & PCF_FOLD_LINE) == 0
730 || line_len + 1 + arg_len < PCF_LINE_LIMIT) {
731 ADD_SPACE;
732 } else {
733 vstream_fputs("\n" PCF_INDENT_TEXT, fp);
734 line_len = PCF_INDENT_LEN;
735 }
736 }
737 if (in_daemon_options == 0 && need_parens)
738 ADD_TEXT("{", 1);
739 ADD_TEXT(arg, strlen(arg));
740 if (in_daemon_options == 0 && need_parens)
741 ADD_TEXT("}", 1);
742 if (aval) {
743 ADD_SPACE;
744 if (need_parens)
745 ADD_TEXT("{", 1);
746 ADD_TEXT(aval, strlen(aval));
747 if (need_parens)
748 ADD_TEXT("}", 1);
749 field += 1;
750
751 /* Force line break after option with value. */
752 line_len = PCF_LINE_LIMIT;
753 }
754 }
755 }
756 vstream_fputs("\n", fp);
757
758 if (msg_verbose)
759 vstream_fflush(fp);
760}
761
762/* pcf_show_master_fields - show master.cf fields */
763
764void pcf_show_master_fields(VSTREAM *fp, int mode, int argc, char **argv)
765{
766 const char *myname = "pcf_show_master_fields";
767 PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp;
768 PCF_MASTER_FLD_REQ *field_reqs;
769 PCF_MASTER_FLD_REQ *req;
770 int field;
771
772 /*
773 * Parse the filter expressions.
774 */
775 if (argc > 0) {
776 field_reqs = (PCF_MASTER_FLD_REQ *)
777 mymalloc(sizeof(*field_reqs) * argc);
778 for (req = field_reqs; req < field_reqs + argc; req++) {
779 req->match_count = 0;
780 req->raw_text = *argv++;
781 req->service_pattern =
782 pcf_parse_service_pattern(req->raw_text, 1, 3);
783 if (req->service_pattern == 0)
784 msg_fatal("-F option requires service_name[/type[/field]]");
785 field = req->field_pattern =
786 pcf_parse_field_pattern(req->service_pattern->argv[2]);
787 if (pcf_is_magic_field_pattern(field) == 0
788 && (field < 0 || field > PCF_MASTER_FLD_CMD))
789 msg_panic("%s: bad attribute field index: %d",
790 myname, field);
791 }
792 }
793
794 /*
795 * Iterate over the master table.
796 */
797 for (masterp = pcf_master_table; masterp->argv != 0; masterp++) {
798 if (argc > 0) {
799 for (req = field_reqs; req < field_reqs + argc; req++) {
800 if (PCF_MATCH_SERVICE_PATTERN(req->service_pattern,
801 masterp->argv->argv[0],
802 masterp->argv->argv[1])) {
803 req->match_count++;
804 field = req->field_pattern;
805 if (pcf_is_magic_field_pattern(field)) {
806 for (field = 0; field <= PCF_MASTER_FLD_CMD; field++)
807 pcf_print_master_field(fp, mode, masterp, field);
808 } else {
809 pcf_print_master_field(fp, mode, masterp, field);
810 }
811 }
812 }
813 } else {
814 for (field = 0; field <= PCF_MASTER_FLD_CMD; field++)
815 pcf_print_master_field(fp, mode, masterp, field);
816 }
817 }
818
819 /*
820 * Cleanup.
821 */
822 if (argc > 0) {
823 for (req = field_reqs; req < field_reqs + argc; req++) {
824 if (req->match_count == 0)
825 msg_warn("unmatched request: \"%s\"", req->raw_text);
826 argv_free(req->service_pattern);
827 }
828 myfree((void *) field_reqs);
829 }
830}
831
832/* pcf_edit_master_field - replace master.cf field value. */
833
834void pcf_edit_master_field(PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp, int field,
835 const char *new_value)
836{
837
838 /*
839 * Replace multi-column attribute.
840 */
841 if (field == PCF_MASTER_FLD_CMD) {
842 argv_truncate(masterp->argv, PCF_MASTER_FLD_CMD);
843 argv_splitq_append(masterp->argv, new_value, PCF_MASTER_BLANKS, CHARS_BRACE);
844 pcf_normalize_daemon_args(masterp->argv);
845 }
846
847 /*
848 * Replace single-column attribute.
849 */
850 else {
851 argv_replace_one(masterp->argv, field, new_value);
852 }
853
854 /*
855 * Do per-field sanity checks.
856 */
857 pcf_check_master_entry(masterp->argv, new_value);
858}

860/* pcf_print_master_param - scaffolding */
861
862static void pcf_print_master_param(VSTREAM *fp, int mode,
863 PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp,
864 const char *param_name,
865 const char *param_value)
866{
867 if (mode & PCF_HIDE_VALUE) {
868 pcf_print_line(fp, mode, "%s%c%s\n",
869 masterp->name_space, PCF_NAMESP_SEP_CH,
870 param_name);
871 } else {
872 if ((mode & PCF_SHOW_EVAL) != 0)
873 param_value = pcf_expand_parameter_value((VSTRING *) 0, mode,
874 param_value, masterp);
875 if ((mode & PCF_HIDE_NAME) == 0) {
876 pcf_print_line(fp, mode, "%s%c%s = %s\n",
877 masterp->name_space, PCF_NAMESP_SEP_CH,
878 param_name, param_value);
879 } else {
880 pcf_print_line(fp, mode, "%s\n", param_value);
881 }
882 }
883 if (msg_verbose)
884 vstream_fflush(fp);
885}
886
887/* pcf_sort_argv_cb - sort argv call-back */
888
889static int pcf_sort_argv_cb(const void *a, const void *b)
890{
891 return (strcmp(*(char **) a, *(char **) b));
892}
893
894/* pcf_show_master_any_param - show any parameter in master.cf service entry */
895
896static void pcf_show_master_any_param(VSTREAM *fp, int mode,
897 PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp)
898{
899 const char *myname = "pcf_show_master_any_param";
900 ARGV *argv = argv_alloc(10);
901 DICT *dict = masterp->all_params;
902 const char *param_name;
903 const char *param_value;
904 int param_count = 0;
905 int how;
906 char **cpp;
907
908 /*
909 * Print parameters in sorted order. The number of parameters per
910 * master.cf entry is small, so we optmiize for code simplicity and don't
911 * worry about the cost of double lookup.
912 */
913
914 /* Look up the parameter names and ignore the values. */
915
916 for (how = DICT_SEQ_FUN_FIRST;
917 dict->sequence(dict, how, &param_name, &param_value) == 0;
918 how = DICT_SEQ_FUN_NEXT) {
919 argv_add(argv, param_name, ARGV_END);
920 param_count++;
921 }
922
923 /* Print the parameters in sorted order. */
924
925 qsort(argv->argv, param_count, sizeof(argv->argv[0]), pcf_sort_argv_cb);
926 for (cpp = argv->argv; (param_name = *cpp) != 0; cpp++) {
927 if ((param_value = dict_get(dict, param_name)) == 0)
928 msg_panic("%s: parameter name not found: %s", myname, param_name);
929 pcf_print_master_param(fp, mode, masterp, param_name, param_value);
930 }
931
932 /*
933 * Clean up.
934 */
935 argv_free(argv);
936}
937
938/* pcf_show_master_params - show master.cf params */
939
940void pcf_show_master_params(VSTREAM *fp, int mode, int argc, char **argv)
941{
942 PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp;
943 PCF_MASTER_FLD_REQ *field_reqs;
944 PCF_MASTER_FLD_REQ *req;
945 DICT *dict;
946 const char *param_value;
947
948 /*
949 * Parse the filter expressions.
950 */
951 if (argc > 0) {
952 field_reqs = (PCF_MASTER_FLD_REQ *)
953 mymalloc(sizeof(*field_reqs) * argc);
954 for (req = field_reqs; req < field_reqs + argc; req++) {
955 req->match_count = 0;
956 req->raw_text = *argv++;
957 req->service_pattern =
958 pcf_parse_service_pattern(req->raw_text, 1, 3);
959 if (req->service_pattern == 0)
960 msg_fatal("-P option requires service_name[/type[/parameter]]");
961 req->param_pattern = req->service_pattern->argv[2];
962 }
963 }
964
965 /*
966 * Iterate over the master table.
967 */
968 for (masterp = pcf_master_table; masterp->argv != 0; masterp++) {
969 if ((dict = masterp->all_params) != 0) {
970 if (argc > 0) {
971 for (req = field_reqs; req < field_reqs + argc; req++) {
972 if (PCF_MATCH_SERVICE_PATTERN(req->service_pattern,
973 masterp->argv->argv[0],
974 masterp->argv->argv[1])) {
975 if (PCF_IS_MAGIC_PARAM_PATTERN(req->param_pattern)) {
976 pcf_show_master_any_param(fp, mode, masterp);
977 req->match_count += 1;
978 } else if ((param_value = dict_get(dict,
979 req->param_pattern)) != 0) {
980 pcf_print_master_param(fp, mode, masterp,
981 req->param_pattern,
982 param_value);
983 req->match_count += 1;
984 }
985 }
986 }
987 } else {
988 pcf_show_master_any_param(fp, mode, masterp);
989 }
990 }
991 }
992
993 /*
994 * Cleanup.
995 */
996 if (argc > 0) {
997 for (req = field_reqs; req < field_reqs + argc; req++) {
998 if (req->match_count == 0)
999 msg_warn("unmatched request: \"%s\"", req->raw_text);
1000 argv_free(req->service_pattern);
1001 }
1002 myfree((void *) field_reqs);
1003 }
1004}
1005
1006/* pcf_edit_master_param - update, add or remove -o parameter=value */
1007
1008void pcf_edit_master_param(PCF_MASTER_ENT *masterp, int mode,
1009 const char *param_name,
1010 const char *param_value)
1011{
1012 const char *myname = "pcf_edit_master_param";
1013 ARGV *argv = masterp->argv;
1014 const char *arg;
1015 const char *aval;
1016 int param_match = 0;
1017 int name_len = strlen(param_name);
1018 int field;
1019
1020 for (field = PCF_MASTER_MIN_FIELDS; argv->argv[field] != 0; field++) {
1021 arg = argv->argv[field];
1022
1023 /*
1024 * Stop at the first non-option argument or end-of-list.
1025 */
1026 if (arg[0] != '-' || strcmp(arg, "--") == 0) {
1027 break;
1028 }
1029
1030 /*
1031 * Zoom in on command-line options with a value.
1032 */
1033 else if (strchr(pcf_daemon_options_expecting_value, arg[1]) != 0
1034 && (aval = argv->argv[field + 1]) != 0) {
1035
1036 /*
1037 * Zoom in on "-o parameter=value".
1038 */
1039 if (strcmp(arg, "-o") == 0) {
1040 if (strncmp(aval, param_name, name_len) == 0
1041 && aval[name_len] == '=') {
1042 param_match = 1;
1043 switch (mode & (PCF_EDIT_CONF | PCF_EDIT_EXCL)) {
1044
1045 /*
1046 * Update parameter=value.
1047 */
1048 case PCF_EDIT_CONF:
1049 aval = concatenate(param_name, "=",
1050 param_value, (char *) 0);
1051 argv_replace_one(argv, field + 1, aval);
1052 myfree((void *) aval);
1053 if (masterp->all_params)
1054 dict_put(masterp->all_params, param_name, param_value);
1055 /* XXX Update parameter "used/defined" status. */
1056 break;
1057
1058 /*
1059 * Delete parameter=value.
1060 */
1061 case PCF_EDIT_EXCL:
1062 argv_delete(argv, field, 2);
1063 if (masterp->all_params)
1064 dict_del(masterp->all_params, param_name);
1065 /* XXX Update parameter "used/defined" status. */
1066 field -= 2;
1067 break;
1068 default:
1069 msg_panic("%s: unexpected mode: %d", myname, mode);
1070 }
1071 }
1072 }
1073
1074 /*
1075 * Skip over the command-line option value.
1076 */
1077 field += 1;
1078 }
1079 }
1080
1081 /*
1082 * Add unmatched parameter.
1083 */
1084 if ((mode & PCF_EDIT_CONF) && param_match == 0) {
1085 /* XXX Generalize: argv_insert(argv, where, list...) */
1086 argv_insert_one(argv, field, "-o");
1087 aval = concatenate(param_name, "=",
1088 param_value, (char *) 0);
1089 argv_insert_one(argv, field + 1, aval);
1090 if (masterp->all_params)
1091 dict_put(masterp->all_params, param_name, param_value);
1092 /* XXX May affect parameter "used/defined" status. */
1093 myfree((void *) aval);
1094 param_match = 1;
1095 }
1096}
